DomainData.MainInfoText:
When you use our online services, we and our third party partners may collect some info about you, your preferences, or your device using technologies such as cookies, pixels, and others (collectively, “cookies”). Other than technologies that are required to use our services, you can manage your preferences for certain categories as described below. Click on each category for more information.

If you don’t want to share your personal info for advertising based on your activity on other websites and services, you can turn off “Retargeting or advertising cookies” in your preferences. For more info, visit our Privacy Notice below.
DomainData.AlertNoticeText: We and our partners may use cookies and similar technologies (“cookies”) for site performance, analytics, advertising, and more. Some are required to use our website and can’t be turned off. For more info, including how to manage your consent for optional cookies, visit Cookie Preferences.
DomainData.AlertMoreInfoTextDialog: Manage preferences, Opens the preference center dialog
DomainData.CookieListDescription: A cookie is a small piece of data (text file) that a website – when visited by a user – asks your browser to store on your device in order to remember information about you, such as your language preference or login information. Those cookies are set by us and called first-party cookies. We also use third-party cookies – which are cookies from a domain different than the domain of the website you are visiting – for our advertising and marketing efforts. More specifically, we use cookies and other tracking technologies for the following purposes:

Groups.GroupDescription: These cookies are necessary to enable core services like secure login, cookie preferences, identity management, and fraud prevention. They cannot be turned off.

FirstPartyCookies.Name: __ps_sr
FirstPartyCookies.description: This cookie name is used to manage user opt-out preferences for non-functional cookies.

FirstPartyCookies.Name: OptanonConsent
FirstPartyCookies.description: This cookie is set by the cookie compliance solution from OneTrust. It stores information about the categories of cookies the site uses and whether visitors have given or withdrawn consent for the use of each category. This enables site owners to prevent cookies in each category from being set in the users browser, when consent is not given. The cookie has a normal lifespan of one year, so that returning visitors to the site will have their preferences remembered. It contains no information that can identify the site visitor.

FirstPartyCookies.Name: _ga
FirstPartyCookies.description: This cookie name is associated with Google Universal Analytics - which is a significant update to Google's more commonly used analytics service. This cookie is used to distinguish unique users by assigning a randomly generated number as a client identifier. It is included in each page request in a site and used to calculate visitor, session and campaign data for the sites analytics reports. By default it is set to expire after 2 years, although this is customisable by website owners. For more information about Google's processing of your personal data, please consult Google's Privacy & Terms site.

FirstPartyCookies.Name: _dd_s
FirstPartyCookies.description: Datadog Cookie used to group all events generated from a unique user session across multiple pages. It contains the current session ID, whether the session is excluded due to sampling, and the expiration date of the session. The cookie is extended for an extra 15 minutes every time the user interacts with the website, up to the maximum user session duration (4 hours).
